All Known Implementing Classes:
ArrayTuple, BinaryPair, Decimal2, Decimal3, Decimal4, DecimalQuaternion, Integer2, Integer3, Integer4, ModelFace, Pair, Quad, QuaternaryQuad, TernaryTriple, Triple
public interface Tuple<E,T extends Tuple<E,T>> extends Group<E>, Iterable<E>, Serializable
An immutable group of elements. A tuple's length or component values cannot be changed after instantiation.

Moebius tuples are very similar to Python tuples in that they are shallowly immutable. Tuples can be iterated by a for-each loop, or by a for-i loop. (using get(int))

Since tuples cannot be resized or modified, nested tuples can effectively create an unmodifiable n-dimensional matrix. (although this is not very efficient, and lacks the functionality of dedicated matrices)
